Hummus

Traditional
1lb dried chickpeas, soaked overnight and drained
1 tbsp kosher salt + more to taste
1 tsp baking soda
1/2 c tahini (Soom)
6 tbsp lemon juice
6 tbsp olive oil + more for garnish
4 garlic cloves, mashed into a paste
freshly ground black pepper to taste

In a 4 quart pot, cover the drained chickpeas with 2" of cold water. Stir in the salt and baking soda, then bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to a simmer and cook until the chickpeas are tender, 45-50 min. Drain the beans, reserving 2 tbsp of the liquid. Transfer the cooked beans to the bowl of a food processor. Add the reserved cooking liquid, tahini, lemon juice, olive oil, and garlic. Puree until smooth, then season with salt and pepper. Transfer to a serving dish and garnish with olive oil.


Pink
2 medium roasted red beets, peeled and roughly chopped
1/4 c olive oil
2 tbsp basalmic vinegar
traditional hummus

In a blender, puree the beets, olive oil, and vinegar until smooth, scraping as needed. Stir into hummus.


Yellow
2 medium carrots, grated
1/2 c olive oil
2 tbsp white prepared horseradish
2 tbsp orange juice
2 tsp tumeric
traditional hummus

In a blender, puree the carrots, olive oil, horseradish, oj, and tumeric until smooth, scraping as needed. Stir into hummmus.


Green
2 c fresh or frozen peas
2 c pea tendrils
1/4 c chervil
1/4 c olive oil
2 tbsp lemon juice
traditional hummus

In a blender, puree the peas, pea tendrils, chervil, olive oil, and lemon juice until smooth, scraping as needed. Stir into hummus.


Orange
2 roasted red peppers (1c)
1/4 c harissa
1/2 c olive oil
1 tbsp sweet paprika
traditional hummus

In a blender, puree the peppers, harissa, olive oil, and paprika until smooth, scraping as needed. Stir into hummus.
